# C++ style (`src/`)

## `[[nodiscard]]`

Use only when ignoring the return risks **bugs, leaks, or broken invariants** (ownership handles, required status, protocol steps). Avoid on benign getters or debug helpers. Do not change generated `src/Codegen/*_gen.hpp` attributes unless codegen does.

## Class member order (per access section)

Within each `public:` / `protected:` / `private:` block, declare **virtual overrides** (`override` / `override final`) **above** other **member functions** in that block. Constructors, destructors, `static` methods, and ordinary methods stay below the override group. Do not reorder across access sections; nested types / data members: follow file style. Do not reorder generated or third-party headers.
